{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_66","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Requirements handoff lifecycle**: integrate the new requirements dispatch modes with the daemon task state machine and the existing project/workflow handoff.\nCurrent: `process_task` routes `requirements_quick` and `requirements_draft` before claim/activate, but the follow-on helpers only allow `active -> waiting_for_requirements` and `active -> completed`. In a temp workspace, a watched issue containing `/rb requirements quick` left the task `pending` with a linked `requirements_run_id` and no project under `.ralph-burning/projects/`; a watched issue containing `/rb requirements draft` failed immediately with `requirements_linking_failed` on `pending -> waiting_for_requirements`.\nExpected: `requirements_quick` must persist the linked requirements run, derive the seed, and continue through project creation/workflow execution in the same daemon cycle. `requirements_draft` must durably enter `waiting_for_requirements`, and when answers are complete the next daemon cycle must derive the seed handoff before any project/worktree mutation.\nReference: loop-16 acceptance criteria for `requirements_quick`, `requirements_draft`, waiting-state invariants, and resume behavior; [daemon_loop.rs#L292](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L292), [daemon_loop.rs#L417](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L417), [daemon_loop.rs#L513](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L513), [task_service.rs#L406](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs#L406), [task_service.rs#L430](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs#L430), [model.rs#L171](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/model.rs#L171), [daemon_loop.rs#L713](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L713)\n\n2. **Requirements command ingestion**: separate requirements-command parsing from flow routing and reject malformed requirements commands instead of silently falling back to workflow dispatch.\nCurrent: `parse_requirements_command` only errors on unknown 3-token variants, so malformed input like `/rb requirements` falls through to `DispatchMode::Workflow`. Also, if `/rb requirements quick` is supplied via `routing_command`, the same field is passed into flow resolution and ingestion fails with a routing error instead of entering the requirements path.\nExpected: unknown or malformed requirements commands must fail ingestion with explicit diagnostics and create no task. Valid requirements commands must still honor flow precedence via `/rb flow <flow-id>` over labels over repo default.\nReference: loop-16 acceptance criterion \"Unknown or malformed requirements commands fail ingestion with explicit diagnostics and create no task\"; [watcher.rs#L26](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/watcher.rs#L26), [watcher.rs#L54](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/watcher.rs#L54), [task_service.rs#L347](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/task_service.rs#L347), [routing.rs#L44](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/routing.rs#L44)\n\n3. **Conformance coverage**: replace the placeholder DAEMON-INTAKE executors with real scenario assertions.\nCurrent: the new feature file describes watcher ingestion, idempotent re-polling, quick/draft handoff, duplicate rejection, and routed-flow override, but the registered scenario executors just run `daemon status` and assert success. `./target/debug/ralph-burning conformance run --filter DAEMON-INTAKE-003` passes even though the quick handoff behavior above does not satisfy the spec.\nExpected: conformance must actually create watched issues/tasks, run daemon cycles, and assert the durable task/project/requirements state required by each DAEMON-INTAKE scenario, while retaining the `SC-PROJ-009` fixture repair.\nReference: loop-16 acceptance criterion \"Add conformance coverage ... and require `cargo run -- conformance run` to pass end-to-end afterward\"; [daemon_issue_intake.feature#L22](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature#L22), [scenarios.rs#L5524](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5524)"}}
