{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_126","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Requirements draft lifecycle / public gate**: `requirements_draft` still does not meet the interactive draft contract end-to-end.\nCurrent: `nix develop -c cargo run -- conformance run` fails on `RD-001` with `expected 'awaiting_answers', got 'completed'`. The default requirements stub returns an empty question set for every draft request in [stub_backend.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs#L376), so [service.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/requirements_drafting/service.rs#L253) skips straight to completion. The daemon then unconditionally moves `/rb requirements draft` tasks into waiting in [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L603), which I reproduced locally: the task was `waiting_for_requirements` while its linked requirements `run.json` was already `completed`.\nExpected: normal draft mode must reach `awaiting_answers` for the non-empty-question path, and daemon tasks should only enter waiting when user answers are actually pending; the full conformance gate must pass afterward.\nReference: loop-16 acceptance criteria for `requirements_draft` waiting/resume and end-to-end `cargo run -- conformance run`; [requirements_drafting.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/requirements_drafting.feature#L8)\n\n2. **Flow-override warning recording**: routed-flow overrides are only printed, not recorded.\nCurrent: both [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L254) and [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L532) only `println!` when the seed suggests a different flow. Neither the task’s `routing_warnings` field in [model.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/model.rs#L64) nor the daemon journal gets a warning entry. A manual `/rb flow quick_dev` + `requirements quick` repro produced the stdout warning but no persisted warning in task JSON or `journal.ndjson`.\nExpected: the override warning should be persisted on the task and/or journal so it survives beyond ephemeral runtime logs, while keeping the routed flow authoritative.\nReference: acceptance criterion “record a warning” for routed-flow overrides; [daemon_issue_intake.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature#L49)\n\n3. **DAEMON-INTAKE conformance fidelity**: the new conformance scenarios still do not exercise the behaviors the feature file promises.\nCurrent: `DAEMON-INTAKE-003` stops after task creation and `daemon status` in [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5608); `DAEMON-INTAKE-004` manually mutates task state instead of running the daemon/requirements path in [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5657); `DAEMON-INTAKE-006` checks only initial routing in [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5762); `DAEMON-INTAKE-007` only exercises the parser in [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5796). Those pass even when the real handoff/warning behavior drifts.\nExpected: these scenarios should execute the actual watcher + daemon + requirements flow and assert durable task/project/requirements state for quick handoff, draft waiting/resume, malformed-command ingestion rejection, duplicate rejection, and routed-flow override.\nReference: loop-16 acceptance criterion “Add conformance coverage for ...”; [daemon_issue_intake.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature#L23)\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add a failure-injection test around the first quick-path task link in [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L498). A `write_task`/journal failure there would currently bubble out of the daemon cycle before the task is marked `failed`, which is an explicit invariant in the spec but is not covered today."}}
