{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_16","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' 20260313001001-impl-notes.md\"","aggregated_output":"# Implementation Notes\n\n## Decisions Made\n- Added durable rollback checkpoints as first-class persisted records under `projects/<project-id>/rollback/`, and emitted matching `rollback_created` journal events so visible rollback history can be reconstructed from the append-only journal.\n- Implemented rollback history filtering as journal replay logic that prunes abandoned branches on each `rollback_performed` event, which lets `run history`, `run tail`, and `run resume` hide rolled-back work while still showing new work after a rollback.\n- Captured rollback checkpoints only at durable stage-transition boundaries after snapshot/journal transition side effects completed, so restoring a checkpoint yields a resumable state the engine can actually reconstruct.\n- Made hard rollback best-effort on the repository side only after the logical rollback is durable in `run.json` and `journal.ndjson`, preserving the required ordering invariant even when `git reset --hard` fails.\n- Hardened filesystem NDJSON appends to insert a separator newline when the existing file lacks a trailing newline, preventing rollback journal appends from corrupting existing history files.\n\n## Spec Deviations\n- None.\n\n## Testing\n- Verified with `nix develop -c cargo test`.\n\n---\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
