{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_61","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **End-to-end conformance gate**: the explicit public-gate acceptance criterion is still unmet.\n   - Current: `nix develop -c cargo test` passes, but `nix develop -c cargo run -- conformance run` still exits non-zero on `SC-CR-001` with `invalid type: map, expected a string`. The scenario injects structured amendment objects for `completion_panel`, while the validation payload still deserializes `follow_up_or_amendments` as `Vec<String>`.\n   - Expected: `cargo run -- conformance run` must pass end-to-end. `SC-CR-001` needs to accept the scenario’s amendment-shaped payload or the scenario/contract needs to be brought back into alignment so the completion-round path actually runs.\n   - Reference: loop-16 acceptance criterion “require `cargo run -- conformance run` to pass end-to-end afterward”; [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L1926), [payloads.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/payloads.rs#L87), [run_completion_rounds.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/run_completion_rounds.feature#L7)\n\n2. **Requirements-link failure invariant**: task-link persistence can still fail without transitioning the task to `failed`.\n   - Current: after `quick()`/`draft()` succeeds, the first task-link writes and handoff journal appends use `?` directly. If `write_task` or `append_journal_event` fails at those points, the daemon returns early and leaves an addressable requirements run without the task being marked `failed` with an explicit linking failure class.\n   - Expected: when requirements-run creation succeeds but linking that run back to the task fails, the task must transition to `failed` with an explicit linking failure class before returning, and no project/worktree state should be created.\n   - Reference: loop-16 acceptance criterion “if a requirements run is created but linking it back to the task fails, the task transitions to `failed` with an explicit failure class”; [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L508), [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L514), [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L637), [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L642)\n\n3. **Daemon-intake conformance fidelity**: the new scenarios still do not cover the full public behavior promised by the feature and spec.\n   - Current: `DAEMON-INTAKE-003`’s feature says the task “transitions to completed”, but the executor explicitly tolerates workflow/worktree failure and only checks that the requirements run completed and metadata was written. `DAEMON-INTAKE-004` covers entry into `waiting_for_requirements`, but there is still no daemon-side conformance scenario for `requirements answer <run-id>` followed by the next daemon cycle resuming the waiting task.\n   - Expected: conformance should exercise the real watcher → daemon → requirements → workflow path for quick handoff, and it should add a daemon-level waiting/resume scenario that proves `requirements answer` unblocks the next cycle.\n   - Reference: loop-16 acceptance criterion “Add conformance coverage for … `requirements_quick` handoff, `requirements_draft` waiting/resume behavior …”; [daemon_issue_intake.feature](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/daemon_issue_intake.feature#L22), [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5608), [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L5693)\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add failure-injection tests around the first requirements-link `write_task`/journal append in both quick and draft paths so the invariant from item 2 stays protected."}}
