{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_72","type":"agent_message","text":"# Review: SUGGESTIONS\n\n## Required Changes\n1. **Public conformance entrypoint**\n   - Current: `nix develop -c cargo run -- conformance run` still fails immediately on scenario 1 with `failed to run CLI: No such file or directory (os error 2)`. The runner respawns `current_exe()` and then changes into a temp workspace; under `cargo run`, that path is not robust enough for the child process launch.\n   - Expected: the conformance runner must resolve the CLI binary to an absolute/canonical path so `cargo run -- conformance run` passes end-to-end, as the spec requires.\n   - Reference: acceptance criterion “require `cargo run -- conformance run` to pass end-to-end afterward”; [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L44), [scenarios.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/conformance_spec/scenarios.rs#L63)\n\n2. **`requirements_draft` empty-question handoff**\n   - Current: a watched issue with `/rb requirements draft` and the default stub backend leaves the task in `status: \"active\"` with `dispatch_mode: \"workflow\"` and a linked `requirements_run_id`, but no project is created; a second daemon cycle does nothing because the loop only processes `pending` tasks. The code returns early for all `RequirementsDraft` tasks, and the empty-question branch never requeues the task or falls through to workflow dispatch.\n   - Expected: if `draft()` completes without questions, the daemon must either continue into project/workflow execution in the same cycle or transition the task back to `pending` for the next cycle. It must not strand an `active` task with no lease, no worktree, and no active workflow run.\n   - Reference: daemon requirements-handoff acceptance criteria; [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L166), [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L371), [daemon_loop.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/automation_runtime/daemon_loop.rs#L696), [stub_backend.rs](/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/stub_backend.rs#L376)\n\n## Recommended Improvements\n1. Add conformance or unit coverage for the empty-question `requirements_draft` branch. The current suite covers the non-empty waiting/resume path, but it does not protect the immediate-completion path that now strands tasks."}}
